annotationA: FI17138p1; Spaghetti is a TPR domain-containing cochaperone that associates with Hsp70 and Hsp90 in flies or human to regulate their activity in macromolecular complexes like RNA polymerase, ribonucleoproteins and Phosphatidyl-Inositol 3-kinase-related kinases. It has been shown to regulate dco levels, with consequences for circadian rhythms and apoptosis
annotationB: RuvB-like helicase 1; Acts as a transcriptional coactivator in Wg signaling caused by altered arm signaling. Pont and rept interfere antagonistically with nuclear arm signaling function, and are required to enhance or reduce arm activity, respectively. Also an essential cofactor for the normal function of Myc; required for cellular proliferation and growth
